\section{Description}
\label{description::doc}\label{description:description}
This is a set of packages and scripts that provides a simple way for programmatically interfacing with Tanium's SOAP API. It is comprised of four parts:
\begin{itemize}
\item {} 
Tanium Server SOAP API: The SOAP server embedded into the Tanium server itself, listens on port 444 but is also available via port 443.

\item {} 
TaniumPy Python Package ({\hyperref[taniumpy:module-taniumpy]{\code{taniumpy}}}): A python package comprised of a set of python objects automatically generated from the WSDL file that describes the Tanium SOAP API. These python objects handle the serialization and deserialization of XML to and from the Tanium Server SOAP API. Located in \code{lib/taniumpy}

\item {} 
PyTan Python Package: ({\hyperref[pytan:module-pytan]{\code{pytan}}}): A python package that provides a set of methods to make interfacing with TaniumPy more human friendly. Located in \code{lib/pytan}

\item {} 
PyTan Command Line Scripts: A set of command line scripts that utilize the PyTan Package ({\hyperref[pytan:module-pytan]{\code{pytan}}}) to make it easy for non-programmers to create/get/delete/ask/deploy objects via the Tanium Server SOAP API.

\end{itemize}


\section{Why it was created}
\label{description:why-it-was-created}
This was created to solve for the following needs:
\begin{itemize}
\item {} 
Create a python package ({\hyperref[pytan:module-pytan]{\code{pytan}}}) to provide a set of methods for making it easier to programmatically interface with Tanium via the SOAP API.

\item {} 
Create a set of command line scripts utilizing the {\hyperref[pytan:module-pytan]{\code{pytan}}} package that handle the argument parsing, thereby providing non-programmers with command line access to the functionality therein.

\item {} 
Provide a way to ask questions and get results via Python and/or the command line.

\item {} 
Provide a way to deploy actions and get results via Python and/or the command line.

\item {} 
Provide a way to export/import objects in JSON via Python and/or the command line.

\end{itemize}


\section{Requirements}
\label{description:requirements}\begin{itemize}
\item {} 
Python 2.7

\item {} 
A working install of Tanium Server 6.2

\end{itemize}


\section{Installation}
\label{description:installation}\begin{description}
\item[{Windows Installation}] \leavevmode\begin{itemize}
\item {} 
Download Python 2.7 from \href{https://www.python.org/downloads/windows/}{https://www.python.org/downloads/windows/}

\item {} 
Install Python 2.7 -- if you accept the default paths it will install to \code{C:\textbackslash{}Python27}

\item {} 
Copy PyTan from github to your local machine somewhere

\item {} 
If you did not accept the default install path for Python 2.7, edit \code{pytan\textbackslash{}winbin\textbackslash{}CONFIG.bat} to change the \emph{PYTHON} variable to point to the full path of \emph{python.exe}

\end{itemize}

\item[{OS X Installation}] \leavevmode\begin{itemize}
\item {} 
OS X 10.8 and higher come with Python 2.7 out of the box

\item {} 
Copy PyTan from github to your local machine somewhere

\end{itemize}

\item[{Linux Installation}] \leavevmode\begin{itemize}
\item {} 
Ensure Python 2.7 is installed

\item {} 
Ensure the first \emph{python} binary in your path points to your Python 2.7 installation

\item {} 
Copy PyTan from github to your local machine somewhere

\end{itemize}

\end{description}


\section{Usage}
\label{description:usage}\begin{itemize}
\item {} 
For command line usage, refer to Command Line Help Index

\item {} 
For API Examples, refer to the {\hyperref[examples/pytan_examples::doc]{\emph{pytan API examples}}}

\item {} 
For in depth API Documentation, refer to the {\hyperref[pytan::doc]{\emph{pytan package}}}, especially the {\hyperref[pytan.handler::doc]{\emph{pytan.handler module}}}

\end{itemize}

\subsubsection{Pytan api basic handler example}
\label{examples/pytan_api_basic_handler_example:pytan-api-basic-handler-example}\label{examples/pytan_api_basic_handler_example::doc}
Here is an example for how to instantiate a \code{pytan.Handler} object.

The username, password, host, and maybe port as well need to be provided on a per Tanium server basis.


\paragraph{Example Python Code}
\label{examples/pytan_api_basic_handler_example:example-python-code}
\begin{Verbatim}[frame=single,commandchars=\\\{\},numbers=left,firstnumber=1,stepnumber=1]
\PYG{c}{\PYGZsh{} Path to lib directory which contains pytan package}
\PYG{n}{PYTAN\PYGZus{}LIB\PYGZus{}PATH} \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{l+s}{\PYGZsq{}}\PYG{l+s}{../lib}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZsq{}}

\PYG{c}{\PYGZsh{} connection info for Tanium Server}
\PYG{n}{USERNAME} \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}\PYG{l+s}{Tanium User}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}
\PYG{n}{PASSWORD} \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}\PYG{l+s}{T@n!um}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}
\PYG{n}{HOST} \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}\PYG{l+s}{172.16.31.128}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}
\PYG{n}{PORT} \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}\PYG{l+s}{444}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}

\PYG{c}{\PYGZsh{} Logging conrols}
\PYG{n}{LOGLEVEL} \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{l+m+mi}{2}
\PYG{n}{DEBUGFORMAT} \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{n+nb+bp}{False}

\PYG{k+kn}{import} \PYG{n+nn}{sys}\PYG{o}{,} \PYG{n+nn}{tempfile}
\PYG{n}{sys}\PYG{o}{.}\PYG{n}{path}\PYG{o}{.}\PYG{n}{append}\PYG{p}{(}\PYG{n}{PYTAN\PYGZus{}LIB\PYGZus{}PATH}\PYG{p}{)}

\PYG{n}{handler} \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{n}{pytan}\PYG{o}{.}\PYG{n}{Handler}\PYG{p}{(}
    \PYG{n}{username}\PYG{o}{=}\PYG{n}{USERNAME}\PYG{p}{,}
    \PYG{n}{password}\PYG{o}{=}\PYG{n}{PASSWORD}\PYG{p}{,}
    \PYG{n}{host}\PYG{o}{=}\PYG{n}{HOST}\PYG{p}{,}

\paragraph{Ask saved question by name}
\label{examples/ask_saved_question_by_name::doc}\label{examples/ask_saved_question_by_name:ask-saved-question-by-name}
Ask a saved question by referencing the name of a saved question in a string.


\subparagraph{Example Python Code}
\label{examples/ask_saved_question_by_name:example-python-code}
\begin{Verbatim}[frame=single,commandchars=\\\{\},numbers=left,firstnumber=1,stepnumber=1]

\PYG{n}{PORT} \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}\PYG{l+s}{444}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}

\PYG{n}{handler} \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{n}{pytan}\PYG{o}{.}\PYG{n}{Handler}\PYG{p}{(}

\PYG{p}{)}

\PYG{k}{print} \PYG{n}{handler}

\PYG{n}{kwargs}\PYG{p}{[}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}\PYG{l+s}{qtype}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}\PYG{p}{]} \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{l+s}{u\PYGZsq{}}\PYG{l+s}{saved}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZsq{}}

\paragraph{Ask manual human question simple single sensor}
\label{examples/ask_manual_human_question_simple_single_sensor:ask-manual-human-question-simple-single-sensor}\label{examples/ask_manual_human_question_simple_single_sensor::doc}
Ask a manual question using human strings by referencing the name of a single sensor in a string.

No sensor filters, sensor parameters, sensor filter options, question filters, or question options supplied.

\paragraph{Ask manual human question multiple sensors identified by name}
\label{examples/ask_manual_human_question_multiple_sensors_identified_by_name:ask-manual-human-question-multiple-sensors-identified-by-name}\label{examples/ask_manual_human_question_multiple_sensors_identified_by_name::doc}
Ask a manual question using human strings by referencing the name of multiple sensors and providing a selector that tells pytan explicitly that we are providing a name of a sensor.

No sensor filters, sensor parameters, sensor filter options, question filters, or question options supplied.


\subparagraph{Example Python Code}
\label{examples/ask_manual_human_question_multiple_sensors_identified_by_name:example-python-code}
\begin{Verbatim}[frame=single,commandchars=\\\{\},numbers=left,firstnumber=1,stepnumber=1]

\PYG{n}{PASSWORD} \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}\PYG{l+s}{T@n!um}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}
\PYG{n}{HOST} \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}\PYG{l+s}{172.16.31.128}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}
\PYG{n}{PORT} \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}\PYG{l+s}{444}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}

\PYG{n}{handler} \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{n}{pytan}\PYG{o}{.}\PYG{n}{Handler}\PYG{p}{(}
    \PYG{n}{username}\PYG{o}{=}\PYG{n}{USERNAME}\PYG{p}{,}

\paragraph{Ask manual human question sensor with parameters and some supplied parameters}
\label{examples/ask_manual_human_question_sensor_with_parameters_and_some_supplied_parameters:ask-manual-human-question-sensor-with-parameters-and-some-supplied-parameters}\label{examples/ask_manual_human_question_sensor_with_parameters_and_some_supplied_parameters::doc}
Ask a manual question using human strings by referencing the name of a single sensor that takes parameters, but supplying only two of the four parameters that are used by the sensor (and letting pytan automatically determine the appropriate default value for those parameters which require a value and none was supplied).

No sensor filters, sensor parameters, sensor filter options, question filters, or question options supplied.

\paragraph{Ask manual human question sensor with parameters and no supplied parameters}
\label{examples/ask_manual_human_question_sensor_with_parameters_and_no_supplied_parameters::doc}\label{examples/ask_manual_human_question_sensor_with_parameters_and_no_supplied_parameters:ask-manual-human-question-sensor-with-parameters-and-no-supplied-parameters}
Ask a manual question using human strings by referencing the name of a single sensor that takes parameters, but not supplying any parameters (and letting pytan automatically determine the appropriate default value for those parameters which require a value).

No sensor filters, sensor parameters, sensor filter options, question filters, or question options supplied.

\paragraph{Ask manual human question sensor with parameters and filter}
\label{examples/ask_manual_human_question_sensor_with_parameters_and_filter:ask-manual-human-question-sensor-with-parameters-and-filter}\label{examples/ask_manual_human_question_sensor_with_parameters_and_filter::doc}
Ask a manual question using human strings by referencing the name of a single sensor that takes parameters, but supplying only two of the four parameters that are used by the sensor.

Also supply a sensor filter that limits the column data that is shown to values that match the regex `.*Shared.*'.

No sensor filter options, question filters, or question options supplied.


\subparagraph{Example Python Code}
\label{examples/ask_manual_human_question_sensor_with_parameters_and_filter:example-python-code}

\PYG{n}{PASSWORD} \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}\PYG{l+s}{T@n!um}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}
\PYG{n}{HOST} \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}\PYG{l+s}{172.16.31.128}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}
\PYG{n}{PORT} \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}\PYG{l+s}{444}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}

\paragraph{Ask manual human question sensor with filter and 3 options}
\label{examples/ask_manual_human_question_sensor_with_filter_and_3_options:ask-manual-human-question-sensor-with-filter-and-3-options}\label{examples/ask_manual_human_question_sensor_with_filter_and_3_options::doc}
Ask a manual question using human strings by referencing the name of a single sensor.

Also supply a sensor filter that limits the column data that is shown to values that contain Windows (which is short hand for regex match against .*Windows.*).

Also supply filter options that re-fetches any cached data that is older than 3600 seconds, matches all values supplied in the filter, and ignores case for any value match of the filter.

No sensor paramaters, question filters, or question options supplied.

\paragraph{Ask manual question sensor complex}
\label{examples/ask_manual_question_sensor_complex:ask-manual-question-sensor-complex}\label{examples/ask_manual_question_sensor_complex::doc}
This provides an example for asking a manual question without using sensors without using human strings.

It uses the Computer Name and Folder Name Search with RegEx Match sensors.

The second sensor has a single parameter, dirname, with a value of `Program Files'.

The second sensor also has 3 sensor filter options that set the max data age to 3600 seconds, does NOT ignore case, and treats all values as string.

There is also a question filter supplied that limits the rows that are displayed to computers that match an Operating System that contains Windows, and has 3 question filter options supplied that set the max data age to 3600 seconds, does NOT ignore case, and uses `and' to join all question filters.

\paragraph{Deploy action with params against windows computers}
\label{examples/deploy_action_with_params_against_windows_computers:deploy-action-with-params-against-windows-computers}\label{examples/deploy_action_with_params_against_windows_computers::doc}
Deploy an action with parameters against only windows computers using human strings.

This will use the Package `Custom Tagging - Add Tags' and supply two parameters. The second parameter will be ignored because the package in question only requires one parameter.

\paragraph{Create action from json}

\paragraph{Create question from json}
\label{examples/create_question_from_json:create-question-from-json}\label{examples/create_question_from_json::doc}
Export a question object to a JSON file, then create a new question object from the exported JSON file. Questions can not be deleted, so do not delete it. This will, in effect, `re-ask' a question.

\PYG{n}{sys}\PYG{o}{.}\PYG{n}{path}\PYG{o}{.}\PYG{n}{append}\PYG{p}{(}\PYG{n}{PYTAN\PYGZus{}LIB\PYGZus{}PATH}\PYG{p}{)}

\PYG{k+kn}{import} \PYG{n+nn}{pytan}
\PYG{n}{handler} \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{n}{pytan}\PYG{o}{.}\PYG{n}{Handler}\PYG{p}{(}

\PYG{p}{)}

\PYG{k}{print} \PYG{n}{handler}

\PYG{c}{\PYGZsh{} setup the export\PYGZus{}obj kwargs for later}

\PYG{n}{export\PYGZus{}kwargs}\PYG{p}{[}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}\PYG{l+s}{header\PYGZus{}sort}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}\PYG{p}{]} \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{n+nb+bp}{True}
\PYG{n}{export\PYGZus{}kwargs}\PYG{p}{[}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}\PYG{l+s}{export\PYGZus{}format}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}\PYG{p}{]} \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{l+s}{u\PYGZsq{}}\PYG{l+s}{csv}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZsq{}}
\PYG{n}{export\PYGZus{}kwargs}\PYG{p}{[}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}\PYG{l+s}{header\PYGZus{}add\PYGZus{}type}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}\PYG{p}{]} \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{n+nb+bp}{True}
\PYG{n}{export\PYGZus{}kwargs}\PYG{p}{[}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}\PYG{l+s}{expand\PYGZus{}grouped\PYGZus{}columns}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}\PYG{p}{]} \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{n+nb+bp}{True}
\PYG{n}{export\PYGZus{}kwargs}\PYG{p}{[}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}\PYG{l+s}{header\PYGZus{}add\PYGZus{}sensor}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}\PYG{p}{]} \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{n+nb+bp}{True}

    \PYG{p}{]}\PYG{p}{,}
\PYG{p}{\PYGZcb{}}

\paragraph{Export resultset json}
\label{examples/export_resultset_json:export-resultset-json}\label{examples/export_resultset_json::doc}
Export a ResultSet from asking a question as JSON with the default options


\subparagraph{Example Python Code}
\label{examples/export_resultset_json:example-python-code}
\begin{Verbatim}[frame=single,commandchars=\\\{\},numbers=left,firstnumber=1,stepnumber=1]
\PYG{c}{\PYGZsh{} Path to lib directory which contains pytan package}
\PYG{n}{PYTAN\PYGZus{}LIB\PYGZus{}PATH} \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{l+s}{\PYGZsq{}}\PYG{l+s}{../lib}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZsq{}}

\PYG{c}{\PYGZsh{} connection info for Tanium Server}
\PYG{n}{USERNAME} \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}\PYG{l+s}{Tanium User}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}
\PYG{n}{PASSWORD} \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}\PYG{l+s}{T@n!um}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}
\PYG{n}{HOST} \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}\PYG{l+s}{172.16.31.128}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}
\PYG{n}{PORT} \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}\PYG{l+s}{444}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}

\PYG{c}{\PYGZsh{} Logging conrols}
\PYG{n}{LOGLEVEL} \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{l+m+mi}{2}
\PYG{n}{DEBUGFORMAT} \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{n+nb+bp}{False}

\PYG{k+kn}{import} \PYG{n+nn}{sys}\PYG{o}{,} \PYG{n+nn}{tempfile}
\PYG{n}{sys}\PYG{o}{.}\PYG{n}{path}\PYG{o}{.}\PYG{n}{append}\PYG{p}{(}\PYG{n}{PYTAN\PYGZus{}LIB\PYGZus{}PATH}\PYG{p}{)}

\PYG{k+kn}{import} \PYG{n+nn}{pytan}
\PYG{n}{handler} \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{n}{pytan}\PYG{o}{.}\PYG{n}{Handler}\PYG{p}{(}
    \PYG{n}{username}\PYG{o}{=}\PYG{n}{USERNAME}\PYG{p}{,}
    \PYG{n}{password}\PYG{o}{=}\PYG{n}{PASSWORD}\PYG{p}{,}
    \PYG{n}{host}\PYG{o}{=}\PYG{n}{HOST}\PYG{p}{,}
    \PYG{n}{port}\PYG{o}{=}\PYG{n}{PORT}\PYG{p}{,}
    \PYG{n}{loglevel}\PYG{o}{=}\PYG{n}{LOGLEVEL}\PYG{p}{,}
    \PYG{n}{debugformat}\PYG{o}{=}\PYG{n}{DEBUGFORMAT}\PYG{p}{,}
\PYG{p}{)}

\PYG{k}{print} \PYG{n}{handler}

\PYG{c}{\PYGZsh{} setup the export\PYGZus{}obj kwargs for later}
\PYG{n}{export\PYGZus{}kwargs} \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{p}{\PYGZob{}}\PYG{p}{\PYGZcb{}}
\PYG{n}{export\PYGZus{}kwargs}\PYG{p}{[}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}\PYG{l+s}{export\PYGZus{}format}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}\PYG{p}{]} \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{l+s}{u\PYGZsq{}}\PYG{l+s}{json}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZsq{}}

\PYG{c}{\PYGZsh{} ask the question that will provide the resultset that we want to use}
\PYG{n}{ask\PYGZus{}kwargs} \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{p}{\PYGZob{}}
    \PYG{l+s}{\PYGZsq{}}\PYG{l+s}{qtype}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZsq{}}\PYG{p}{:} \PYG{l+s}{\PYGZsq{}}\PYG{l+s}{manual\PYGZus{}human}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZsq{}}\PYG{p}{,}
    \PYG{l+s}{\PYGZsq{}}\PYG{l+s}{sensors}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZsq{}}\PYG{p}{:} \PYG{p}{[}
        \PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}\PYG{l+s}{Computer Name}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}\PYG{p}{,} \PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}\PYG{l+s}{IP Route Details}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}\PYG{p}{,} \PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}\PYG{l+s}{IP Address}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}\PYG{p}{,}
        \PYG{l+s}{\PYGZsq{}}\PYG{l+s}{Folder Name Search with RegEx Match\PYGZob{}dirname=Program Files,regex=.*Shared.*\PYGZcb{}}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZsq{}}\PYG{p}{,}
    \PYG{p}{]}\PYG{p}{,}
\PYG{p}{\PYGZcb{}}
\PYG{n}{response} \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{n}{handler}\PYG{o}{.}\PYG{n}{ask}\PYG{p}{(}\PYG{o}{*}\PYG{o}{*}\PYG{n}{ask\PYGZus{}kwargs}\PYG{p}{)}

\PYG{c}{\PYGZsh{} export the object to a string}
\PYG{c}{\PYGZsh{} (we could just as easily export to a file using export\PYGZus{}to\PYGZus{}report\PYGZus{}file)}
\PYG{n}{export\PYGZus{}kwargs}\PYG{p}{[}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZsq{}}\PYG{l+s}{obj}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZsq{}}\PYG{p}{]} \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{n}{response}\PYG{p}{[}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZsq{}}\PYG{l+s}{question\PYGZus{}results}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZsq{}}\PYG{p}{]}
\PYG{n}{export\PYGZus{}str} \PYG{o}{=} \PYG{n}{handler}\PYG{o}{.}\PYG{n}{export\PYGZus{}obj}\PYG{p}{(}\PYG{o}{*}\PYG{o}{*}\PYG{n}{export\PYGZus{}kwargs}\PYG{p}{)}


\PYG{k}{print} \PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}
\PYG{k}{print} \PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}\PYG{l+s}{print the export\PYGZus{}str returned from export\PYGZus{}obj():}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdq{}}
\PYG{k}{print} \PYG{n}{export\PYGZus{}str}
\end{Verbatim}

\PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; Folder Name Search with RegEx Match
\PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039;========================================
\PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039;@INCLUDE=utils/SensorRandomization/SensorRandomizationFunctions.vbs
Option Explicit

SensorRandomize()

Dim Pattern,strRegExp,strGlobalArg,strCaseSensitiveArg
Dim bGlobal,bCaseSensitive

Pattern = unescape(\PYGZam{}quot;\textbar{}\textbar{}dirname\textbar{}\textbar{}\PYGZam{}quot;)
strRegExp = Trim(Unescape(\PYGZam{}quot;\textbar{}\textbar{}regexp\textbar{}\textbar{}\PYGZam{}quot;))
strGlobalArg = Trim(Unescape(\PYGZam{}quot;\textbar{}\textbar{}global\textbar{}\textbar{}\PYGZam{}quot;))
strCaseSensitiveArg = Trim(Unescape(\PYGZam{}quot;\textbar{}\textbar{}casesensitive\textbar{}\textbar{}\PYGZam{}quot;))

bGlobal = GetTrueFalseArg(\PYGZam{}quot;global\PYGZam{}quot;,strGlobalArg)
bCaseSensitive = GetTrueFalseArg(\PYGZam{}quot;casesensitive\PYGZam{}quot;,strCaseSensitiveArg)

Const SYSTEM\PYGZus{}FOLDER = 1, TEMP\PYGZus{}FOLDER = 2, FOR\PYGZus{}READING = 1

Dim FSO, WshShell, Drives, Drive, TextStream, OutputFilename, strLine

Set FSO = CreateObject(\PYGZam{}quot;Scripting.FileSystemObject\PYGZam{}quot;)
Set WshShell = CreateObject(\PYGZam{}quot;WScript.Shell\PYGZam{}quot;)

OutputFilename = TempName() \PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; a temporary file in system\PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039;s temp dir

\PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; Go through file system, refresh output file for filename
If Not FSO.FileExists(OutputFilename) Then

    If FSO.FileExists(OutputFilename) Then FSO.DeleteFile OutputFilename

    \PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; Get the collection of local drives.
    Set Drives = FSO.Drives
    For Each Drive in Drives
            If Drive.DriveType = 2 Then \PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; 2 = Fixed drive
                    \PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; Run the Dir command that looks for the filename pattern.
                    RunCommand \PYGZam{}quot;dir \PYGZam{}quot; \PYGZam{}amp;Chr(34)\PYGZam{}amp; Drive.DriveLetter \PYGZam{}amp; \PYGZam{}quot;:\PYGZbs{}\PYGZam{}quot; \PYGZam{}amp; Pattern \PYGZam{}amp; Chr(34)\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZam{}quot; /a:D /B /S\PYGZam{}quot;, OutputFilename, true
            End If
    Next
End If

\PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; Open the output file, echo each line, and then close and delete it.
Set TextStream = FSO.OpenTextFile(OutputFileName, FOR\PYGZus{}READING)
Do While Not TextStream.AtEndOfStream
    strLine = TextStream.ReadLine()
    If RegExpMatch(strRegExp,strLine,bGlobal,bCaseSensitive) Then
            WScript.Echo strLine
    End If
Loop


TextStream.Close()

If FSO.FileExists(OutputFileName) Then
    On Error Resume Next
    FSO.DeleteFile OutputFileName, True
    On Error Goto 0
End If

Function RegExpMatch(strPattern,strToMatch,bGlobal,bIsCaseSensitive)

    Dim re
    Set re = New RegExp
    With re
      .Pattern = strPattern
      .Global = bGlobal
      .IgnoreCase = Not bIsCaseSensitive
    End With

    RegExpMatch = re.Test(strToMatch)

End Function \PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039;RegExpMatch


Function GetTrueFalseArg(strArgName,strArgValue)
    \PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; Checks for valid values, will fail with error message

    Dim bArgVal
    bArgVal = False
    Select Case LCase(strArgValue)
            Case \PYGZam{}quot;true\PYGZam{}quot;
                    bArgVal = True
            Case \PYGZam{}quot;yes\PYGZam{}quot;
                    bArgVal = True
            Case \PYGZam{}quot;false\PYGZam{}quot;
                    bArgVal = False
            Case \PYGZam{}quot;no\PYGZam{}quot;
                    bArgVal = False
            Case Else
                    WScript.Echo \PYGZam{}quot;Error: Argument \PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039;\PYGZam{}quot;\PYGZam{}amp;strArgName\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZam{}quot;\PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; must be True or False, quitting\PYGZam{}quot;
                    PrintUsage
    End Select
    GetTrueFalseArg = bArgVal

End Function \PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039;GetTrueFalseArg


\PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; Returns the name of a temporary file in the Temp directory.
Function TempName()
    Dim Result
    Do
            Result = FSO.BuildPath(FSO.GetSpecialFolder(TEMP\PYGZus{}FOLDER), FSO.GetTempName())
            WScript.Sleep 200 \PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039;avoid potential busy loop
    Loop While FSO.FileExists(Result)

    TempName = Result
End Function \PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039;TempName

\PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; Runs a command with Cmd.exe and redirects its output to a temporary
\PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; file. The function returns the name of the temporary file that holds
\PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; the command\PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039;s output.
Function RunCommand(Command, OutputFilename, b64BitNecessary)
    \PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; 64BitNecessary true when you need to examine the 64\PYGZhy{}bit areas like system32
    Dim CommandLine,WshShell,strPRogramFilesx86,strDOSCall,objFSO
    Set objFSO = CreateObject(\PYGZam{}quot;Scripting.FileSystemObject\PYGZam{}quot;)
    Set WshShell = CreateObject(\PYGZam{}quot;WScript.Shell\PYGZam{}quot;)

    strDOSCall = \PYGZam{}quot;\PYGZpc{}ComSpec\PYGZpc{} /C \PYGZam{}quot;

    \PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; if 64\PYGZhy{}bit OS *and* we must examine in 64\PYGZhy{}bit mode to avoid FS Redirection
    strProgramFilesx86=WshShell.ExpandEnvironmentStrings(\PYGZam{}quot;\PYGZpc{}ProgramFiles\PYGZpc{}\PYGZam{}quot;)
    If objFSO.FolderExists(strProgramFilesx86) And b64BitNecessary Then \PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; quick check for x64
            strDOSCall = FixFileSystemRedirectionForPath(WshShell.ExpandEnvironmentStrings(strDOSCall))
    End If

    CommandLine = WshShell.ExpandEnvironmentStrings(strDOSCall \PYGZam{}amp; Command \PYGZam{}amp; \PYGZam{}quot; \PYGZam{}gt;\PYGZam{}gt; \PYGZam{}quot;\PYGZam{}quot;\PYGZam{}quot; \PYGZam{}amp; OutputFileName \PYGZam{}amp; \PYGZam{}quot;\PYGZam{}quot;\PYGZam{}quot;\PYGZam{}quot;)
    WshShell.Run CommandLine, 0, True
End Function \PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039;RunCommand

Function FixFileSystemRedirectionForPath(strFilePath)
\PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; This function will fix a folder location so that
\PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; a 32\PYGZhy{}bit program can be passed the windows\PYGZbs{}system32 directory
\PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; as a parameter.
\PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; Even if the sensor or action runs in 64\PYGZhy{}bit mode, a 32\PYGZhy{}bit
\PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; program called in a 64\PYGZhy{}bit environment cannot access
\PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; the system32 directory \PYGZhy{} it would be redirected to syswow64.
\PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; you would not want to do this for 64\PYGZhy{}bit programs.

    Dim objFSO, strSystem32Location,objShell
    Dim strProgramFilesx86,strNewSystem32Location,strRestOfPath
    Set objFSO = CreateObject(\PYGZam{}quot;Scripting.FileSystemObject\PYGZam{}quot;)
    Set objShell = CreateObject(\PYGZam{}quot;Wscript.Shell\PYGZam{}quot;)

    strProgramFilesx86=objShell.ExpandEnvironmentStrings(\PYGZam{}quot;\PYGZpc{}ProgramFiles\PYGZpc{}\PYGZam{}quot;)

    strFilePath = LCase(strFilePath)
    strSystem32Location = LCase(objFSO.GetSpecialFolder(1))
    strProgramFilesx86=objShell.ExpandEnvironmentStrings(\PYGZam{}quot;\PYGZpc{}ProgramFiles(x86)\PYGZpc{}\PYGZam{}quot;)

    If objFSO.FolderExists(strProgramFilesx86) Then \PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; quick check for x64
            If InStr(strFilePath,strSystem32Location) = 1 Then
                    strRestOfPath = Replace(strFilePath,strSystem32Location,\PYGZam{}quot;\PYGZam{}quot;)
                    strNewSystem32Location = Replace(strSystem32Location,\PYGZam{}quot;system32\PYGZam{}quot;,\PYGZam{}quot;sysnative\PYGZam{}quot;)
                    strFilePath = strNewSystem32Location\PYGZam{}amp;strRestOfPath
            End If
    End If
    FixFileSystemRedirectionForPath = strFilePath

    \PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039;Cleanup
    Set objFSO = Nothing
End Function \PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039;FixFileSystemRedirectionForPath

Function SensorRandomizeRandomSleep(intSleepTime)
\PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; sleeps for a random period of time, intSleepTime is in seconds
\PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; if the sensor randomize flag is on
\PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; RandomizeScalingFactor is a multiplier on the values hardcoded in the sensor
\PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; not typically set but can adjust timings per endpoint, optionally
    Dim intSensorRandomizeWaitTime
    Dim objShell,intRandomizeFlag,strRandomizeRegPath,intRandomizeScalingPercentage
    strRandomizeRegPath = SensorRandomizeGetTaniumRegistryPath\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZam{}quot;\PYGZbs{}Sensor Data\PYGZbs{}Random Sleep\PYGZam{}quot;

    Set objShell = CreateObject(\PYGZam{}quot;WScript.Shell\PYGZam{}quot;)
    On Error Resume Next
    intRandomizeFlag = objShell.RegRead(\PYGZam{}quot;HKLM\PYGZbs{}\PYGZam{}quot;\PYGZam{}amp;strRandomizeRegPath\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZam{}quot;\PYGZbs{}SensorRandomizeFlag\PYGZam{}quot;)
    intRandomizeScalingPercentage = objShell.RegRead(\PYGZam{}quot;HKLM\PYGZbs{}\PYGZam{}quot;\PYGZam{}amp;strRandomizeRegPath\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZam{}quot;\PYGZbs{}SensorRandomizeScalingPercentage\PYGZam{}quot;)
    On Error Goto 0
    If intRandomizeFlag \PYGZam{}gt; 0 Then
            If intRandomizeScalingPercentage \PYGZam{}gt; 0 Then
                    intSleepTime = intRandomizeScalingPercentage * .01 * intSleepTime
                    SensorRandomizeEcho \PYGZam{}quot;Randomize scaling percentage of \PYGZam{}quot; \PYGZus{}
                            \PYGZam{}amp; intRandomizeScalingPercentage \PYGZam{}amp; \PYGZam{}quot; applied, new sleep time is \PYGZam{}quot; \PYGZam{}amp; intSleepTime
            End If
            intSensorRandomizeWaitTime = CLng(intSleepTime) * 1000 \PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; convert to milliseconds
            \PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; wait random interval between 0 and the max
            Randomize(SensorRandomizeTaniumRandomSeed)
            \PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; assign random value to wait time max value
            intSensorRandomizeWaitTime = Int( ( intSensorRandomizeWaitTime + 1 ) * Rnd )
            SensorRandomizeEcho \PYGZam{}quot;Sleeping for \PYGZam{}quot; \PYGZam{}amp; intSensorRandomizeWaitTime \PYGZam{}amp; \PYGZam{}quot; milliseconds\PYGZam{}quot;
            WScript.Sleep(intSensorRandomizeWaitTime)
            SensorRandomizeEcho \PYGZam{}quot;Done sleeping, continuing ...\PYGZam{}quot;
    Else
            SensorRandomizeEcho \PYGZam{}quot;SensorRandomize Not Enabled \PYGZhy{} No Op\PYGZam{}quot;
    End If
End Function \PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039;SensorRandomizeRandomSleep

Function SensorRandomizeTaniumRandomSeed
\PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; for randomizing sensor code, the default seed is not random enough
    Dim timerNum
    timerNum = Timer()
    If timerNum \PYGZam{}lt; 1 Then
            SensorRandomizeTaniumRandomSeed = (SensorRandomizeGetTaniumComputerID / Timer() * 10 )
    Else
            SensorRandomizeTaniumRandomSeed = SensorRandomizeGetTaniumComputerID / Timer
    End If
End Function \PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039;SensorRandomizeTaniumRandomSeed

Function SensorRandomizeGetTaniumRegistryPath
\PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039;SensorRandomizeGetTaniumRegistryPath works in x64 or x32
\PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039;looks for a valid Path value

    Dim objShell
    Dim keyNativePath, keyWoWPath, strPath, strFoundTaniumRegistryPath

    Set objShell = CreateObject(\PYGZam{}quot;WScript.Shell\PYGZam{}quot;)

    keyNativePath = \PYGZam{}quot;Software\PYGZbs{}Tanium\PYGZbs{}Tanium Client\PYGZam{}quot;
    keyWoWPath = \PYGZam{}quot;Software\PYGZbs{}Wow6432Node\PYGZbs{}Tanium\PYGZbs{}Tanium Client\PYGZam{}quot;

    \PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; first check the Software key (valid for 32\PYGZhy{}bit machines, or 64\PYGZhy{}bit machines in 32\PYGZhy{}bit mode)
    On Error Resume Next
    strPath = objShell.RegRead(\PYGZam{}quot;HKLM\PYGZbs{}\PYGZam{}quot;\PYGZam{}amp;keyNativePath\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZam{}quot;\PYGZbs{}Path\PYGZam{}quot;)
    On Error Goto 0
    strFoundTaniumRegistryPath = keyNativePath

    If strPath = \PYGZam{}quot;\PYGZam{}quot; Then
            \PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; Could not find 32\PYGZhy{}bit mode path, checking Wow6432Node
            On Error Resume Next

Example: C:\PYGZbs{}WINDOWS\PYGZbs{}System32\PYGZlt{}/description\PYGZgt{}\PYGZlt{}string\PYGZus{}hints /\PYGZgt{}\PYGZlt{}subcolumns /\PYGZgt{}\PYGZlt{}metadata\PYGZgt{}\PYGZlt{}item\PYGZgt{}\PYGZlt{}admin\PYGZus{}flag\PYGZgt{}0\PYGZlt{}/admin\PYGZus{}flag\PYGZgt{}\PYGZlt{}name\PYGZgt{}defined\PYGZlt{}/name\PYGZgt{}\PYGZlt{}value\PYGZgt{}McAfee\PYGZlt{}/value\PYGZgt{}\PYGZlt{}/item\PYGZgt{}\PYGZlt{}/metadata\PYGZgt{}\PYGZlt{}parameters /\PYGZgt{}\PYGZlt{}queries\PYGZgt{}\PYGZlt{}query\PYGZgt{}\PYGZlt{}platform\PYGZgt{}Windows\PYGZlt{}/platform\PYGZgt{}\PYGZlt{}script\PYGZus{}type\PYGZgt{}VBScript\PYGZlt{}/script\PYGZus{}type\PYGZgt{}\PYGZlt{}signature /\PYGZgt{}\PYGZlt{}script\PYGZgt{}\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;========================================
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; Folder Name Search with RegEx Match
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;========================================
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;@INCLUDE=utils/SensorRandomization/SensorRandomizationFunctions.vbs
Option Explicit

SensorRandomize()

Dim Pattern,strRegExp,strGlobalArg,strCaseSensitiveArg
Dim bGlobal,bCaseSensitive

Pattern = unescape(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\textbar{}\textbar{}dirname\textbar{}\textbar{}\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)
strRegExp = Trim(Unescape(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\textbar{}\textbar{}regexp\textbar{}\textbar{}\PYGZam{}amp;quot;))
strGlobalArg = Trim(Unescape(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\textbar{}\textbar{}global\textbar{}\textbar{}\PYGZam{}amp;quot;))
strCaseSensitiveArg = Trim(Unescape(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\textbar{}\textbar{}casesensitive\textbar{}\textbar{}\PYGZam{}amp;quot;))

bGlobal = GetTrueFalseArg(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;global\PYGZam{}amp;quot;,strGlobalArg)
bCaseSensitive = GetTrueFalseArg(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;casesensitive\PYGZam{}amp;quot;,strCaseSensitiveArg)

Const SYSTEM\PYGZus{}FOLDER = 1, TEMP\PYGZus{}FOLDER = 2, FOR\PYGZus{}READING = 1

Dim FSO, WshShell, Drives, Drive, TextStream, OutputFilename, strLine

Set FSO = CreateObject(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;Scripting.FileSystemObject\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)
Set WshShell = CreateObject(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;WScript.Shell\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)

OutputFilename = TempName() \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; a temporary file in system\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;s temp dir

\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; Go through file system, refresh output file for filename
If Not FSO.FileExists(OutputFilename) Then

    If FSO.FileExists(OutputFilename) Then FSO.DeleteFile OutputFilename

    \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; Get the collection of local drives.
    Set Drives = FSO.Drives
    For Each Drive in Drives
            If Drive.DriveType = 2 Then \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; 2 = Fixed drive
                    \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; Run the Dir command that looks for the filename pattern.
                    RunCommand \PYGZam{}amp;quot;dir \PYGZam{}amp;quot; \PYGZam{}amp;amp;Chr(34)\PYGZam{}amp;amp; Drive.DriveLetter \PYGZam{}amp;amp; \PYGZam{}amp;quot;:\PYGZbs{}\PYGZam{}amp;quot; \PYGZam{}amp;amp; Pattern \PYGZam{}amp;amp; Chr(34)\PYGZam{}amp;amp;\PYGZam{}amp;quot; /a:D /B /S\PYGZam{}amp;quot;, OutputFilename, true
            End If
    Next
End If

\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; Open the output file, echo each line, and then close and delete it.
Set TextStream = FSO.OpenTextFile(OutputFileName, FOR\PYGZus{}READING)
Do While Not TextStream.AtEndOfStream
    strLine = TextStream.ReadLine()
    If RegExpMatch(strRegExp,strLine,bGlobal,bCaseSensitive) Then
            WScript.Echo strLine
    End If
Loop


TextStream.Close()

If FSO.FileExists(OutputFileName) Then
    On Error Resume Next
    FSO.DeleteFile OutputFileName, True
    On Error Goto 0
End If

Function RegExpMatch(strPattern,strToMatch,bGlobal,bIsCaseSensitive)

    Dim re
    Set re = New RegExp
    With re
      .Pattern = strPattern
      .Global = bGlobal
      .IgnoreCase = Not bIsCaseSensitive
    End With

    RegExpMatch = re.Test(strToMatch)

End Function \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;RegExpMatch


Function GetTrueFalseArg(strArgName,strArgValue)
    \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; Checks for valid values, will fail with error message

    Dim bArgVal
    bArgVal = False
    Select Case LCase(strArgValue)
            Case \PYGZam{}amp;quot;true\PYGZam{}amp;quot;
                    bArgVal = True
            Case \PYGZam{}amp;quot;yes\PYGZam{}amp;quot;
                    bArgVal = True
            Case \PYGZam{}amp;quot;false\PYGZam{}amp;quot;
                    bArgVal = False
            Case \PYGZam{}amp;quot;no\PYGZam{}amp;quot;
                    bArgVal = False
            Case Else
                    WScript.Echo \PYGZam{}amp;quot;Error: Argument \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;amp;strArgName\PYGZam{}amp;amp;\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; must be True or False, quitting\PYGZam{}amp;quot;
                    PrintUsage
    End Select
    GetTrueFalseArg = bArgVal

End Function \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;GetTrueFalseArg


\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; Returns the name of a temporary file in the Temp directory.
Function TempName()
    Dim Result
    Do
            Result = FSO.BuildPath(FSO.GetSpecialFolder(TEMP\PYGZus{}FOLDER), FSO.GetTempName())
            WScript.Sleep 200 \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;avoid potential busy loop
    Loop While FSO.FileExists(Result)

    TempName = Result
End Function \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;TempName

\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; Runs a command with Cmd.exe and redirects its output to a temporary
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; file. The function returns the name of the temporary file that holds
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; the command\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;s output.
Function RunCommand(Command, OutputFilename, b64BitNecessary)
    \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; 64BitNecessary true when you need to examine the 64\PYGZhy{}bit areas like system32
    Dim CommandLine,WshShell,strPRogramFilesx86,strDOSCall,objFSO
    Set objFSO = CreateObject(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;Scripting.FileSystemObject\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)
    Set WshShell = CreateObject(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;WScript.Shell\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)

    strDOSCall = \PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZpc{}ComSpec\PYGZpc{} /C \PYGZam{}amp;quot;

    \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; if 64\PYGZhy{}bit OS *and* we must examine in 64\PYGZhy{}bit mode to avoid FS Redirection
    strProgramFilesx86=WshShell.ExpandEnvironmentStrings(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZpc{}ProgramFiles\PYGZpc{}\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)
    If objFSO.FolderExists(strProgramFilesx86) And b64BitNecessary Then \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; quick check for x64
            strDOSCall = FixFileSystemRedirectionForPath(WshShell.ExpandEnvironmentStrings(strDOSCall))
    End If

    CommandLine = WshShell.ExpandEnvironmentStrings(strDOSCall \PYGZam{}amp;amp; Command \PYGZam{}amp;amp; \PYGZam{}amp;quot; \PYGZam{}amp;gt;\PYGZam{}amp;gt; \PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;quot; \PYGZam{}amp;amp; OutputFileName \PYGZam{}amp;amp; \PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)
    WshShell.Run CommandLine, 0, True
End Function \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;RunCommand

Function FixFileSystemRedirectionForPath(strFilePath)
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; This function will fix a folder location so that
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; a 32\PYGZhy{}bit program can be passed the windows\PYGZbs{}system32 directory
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; as a parameter.
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; Even if the sensor or action runs in 64\PYGZhy{}bit mode, a 32\PYGZhy{}bit
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; program called in a 64\PYGZhy{}bit environment cannot access
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; the system32 directory \PYGZhy{} it would be redirected to syswow64.
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; you would not want to do this for 64\PYGZhy{}bit programs.

    Dim objFSO, strSystem32Location,objShell
    Dim strProgramFilesx86,strNewSystem32Location,strRestOfPath
    Set objFSO = CreateObject(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;Scripting.FileSystemObject\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)
    Set objShell = CreateObject(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;Wscript.Shell\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)

    strProgramFilesx86=objShell.ExpandEnvironmentStrings(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZpc{}ProgramFiles\PYGZpc{}\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)

    strFilePath = LCase(strFilePath)
    strSystem32Location = LCase(objFSO.GetSpecialFolder(1))
    strProgramFilesx86=objShell.ExpandEnvironmentStrings(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZpc{}ProgramFiles(x86)\PYGZpc{}\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)

    If objFSO.FolderExists(strProgramFilesx86) Then \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; quick check for x64
            If InStr(strFilePath,strSystem32Location) = 1 Then
                    strRestOfPath = Replace(strFilePath,strSystem32Location,\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)
                    strNewSystem32Location = Replace(strSystem32Location,\PYGZam{}amp;quot;system32\PYGZam{}amp;quot;,\PYGZam{}amp;quot;sysnative\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)
                    strFilePath = strNewSystem32Location\PYGZam{}amp;amp;strRestOfPath
            End If
    End If
    FixFileSystemRedirectionForPath = strFilePath

    \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;Cleanup
    Set objFSO = Nothing
End Function \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;FixFileSystemRedirectionForPath

Function SensorRandomizeRandomSleep(intSleepTime)
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; sleeps for a random period of time, intSleepTime is in seconds
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; if the sensor randomize flag is on
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; RandomizeScalingFactor is a multiplier on the values hardcoded in the sensor
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; not typically set but can adjust timings per endpoint, optionally
    Dim intSensorRandomizeWaitTime
    Dim objShell,intRandomizeFlag,strRandomizeRegPath,intRandomizeScalingPercentage
    strRandomizeRegPath = SensorRandomizeGetTaniumRegistryPath\PYGZam{}amp;amp;\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZbs{}Sensor Data\PYGZbs{}Random Sleep\PYGZam{}amp;quot;

    Set objShell = CreateObject(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;WScript.Shell\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)
    On Error Resume Next
    intRandomizeFlag = objShell.RegRead(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;HKLM\PYGZbs{}\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;amp;strRandomizeRegPath\PYGZam{}amp;amp;\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZbs{}SensorRandomizeFlag\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)
    intRandomizeScalingPercentage = objShell.RegRead(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;HKLM\PYGZbs{}\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;amp;strRandomizeRegPath\PYGZam{}amp;amp;\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZbs{}SensorRandomizeScalingPercentage\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)
    On Error Goto 0
    If intRandomizeFlag \PYGZam{}amp;gt; 0 Then
            If intRandomizeScalingPercentage \PYGZam{}amp;gt; 0 Then
                    intSleepTime = intRandomizeScalingPercentage * .01 * intSleepTime
                    SensorRandomizeEcho \PYGZam{}amp;quot;Randomize scaling percentage of \PYGZam{}amp;quot; \PYGZus{}
                            \PYGZam{}amp;amp; intRandomizeScalingPercentage \PYGZam{}amp;amp; \PYGZam{}amp;quot; applied, new sleep time is \PYGZam{}amp;quot; \PYGZam{}amp;amp; intSleepTime
            End If
            intSensorRandomizeWaitTime = CLng(intSleepTime) * 1000 \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; convert to milliseconds
            \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; wait random interval between 0 and the max
            Randomize(SensorRandomizeTaniumRandomSeed)
            \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; assign random value to wait time max value
            intSensorRandomizeWaitTime = Int( ( intSensorRandomizeWaitTime + 1 ) * Rnd )
            SensorRandomizeEcho \PYGZam{}amp;quot;Sleeping for \PYGZam{}amp;quot; \PYGZam{}amp;amp; intSensorRandomizeWaitTime \PYGZam{}amp;amp; \PYGZam{}amp;quot; milliseconds\PYGZam{}amp;quot;
            WScript.Sleep(intSensorRandomizeWaitTime)
            SensorRandomizeEcho \PYGZam{}amp;quot;Done sleeping, continuing ...\PYGZam{}amp;quot;
    Else
            SensorRandomizeEcho \PYGZam{}amp;quot;SensorRandomize Not Enabled \PYGZhy{} No Op\PYGZam{}amp;quot;
    End If
End Function \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;SensorRandomizeRandomSleep

Function SensorRandomizeTaniumRandomSeed
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; for randomizing sensor code, the default seed is not random enough
    Dim timerNum
    timerNum = Timer()
    If timerNum \PYGZam{}amp;lt; 1 Then
            SensorRandomizeTaniumRandomSeed = (SensorRandomizeGetTaniumComputerID / Timer() * 10 )
    Else
            SensorRandomizeTaniumRandomSeed = SensorRandomizeGetTaniumComputerID / Timer
    End If
End Function \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;SensorRandomizeTaniumRandomSeed

Function SensorRandomizeGetTaniumRegistryPath
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;SensorRandomizeGetTaniumRegistryPath works in x64 or x32
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;looks for a valid Path value

    Dim objShell
    Dim keyNativePath, keyWoWPath, strPath, strFoundTaniumRegistryPath

    Set objShell = CreateObject(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;WScript.Shell\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)

    keyNativePath = \PYGZam{}amp;quot;Software\PYGZbs{}Tanium\PYGZbs{}Tanium Client\PYGZam{}amp;quot;
    keyWoWPath = \PYGZam{}amp;quot;Software\PYGZbs{}Wow6432Node\PYGZbs{}Tanium\PYGZbs{}Tanium Client\PYGZam{}amp;quot;

    \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; first check the Software key (valid for 32\PYGZhy{}bit machines, or 64\PYGZhy{}bit machines in 32\PYGZhy{}bit mode)
    On Error Resume Next
    strPath = objShell.RegRead(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;HKLM\PYGZbs{}\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;amp;keyNativePath\PYGZam{}amp;amp;\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZbs{}Path\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)
    On Error Goto 0
    strFoundTaniumRegistryPath = keyNativePath

    If strPath = \PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;quot; Then
            \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; Could not find 32\PYGZhy{}bit mode path, checking Wow6432Node
            On Error Resume Next
            strPath = objShell.RegRead(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;HKLM\PYGZbs{}\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;amp;keyWoWPath\PYGZam{}amp;amp;\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZbs{}Path\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)
            On Error Goto 0
            strFoundTaniumRegistryPath = keyWoWPath
    End If

    If Not strPath = \PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;quot; Then
            SensorRandomizeGetTaniumRegistryPath = strFoundTaniumRegistryPath
    Else
            SensorRandomizeGetTaniumRegistryPath = False
            WScript.Echo \PYGZam{}amp;quot;Error: Cannot locate Tanium Registry Path\PYGZam{}amp;quot;
    End If
End Function \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;SensorRandomizeGetTaniumRegistryPath

Function SensorRandomizeGetTaniumComputerID
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; This function gets the Tanium Computer ID
    Dim objShell
    Dim intClientID,strID,strKeyPath,strValueName

    strKeyPath = SensorRandomizeGetTaniumRegistryPath
    strValueName = \PYGZam{}amp;quot;ComputerID\PYGZam{}amp;quot;
    Set objShell = CreateObject(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;WScript.Shell\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)
    On Error Resume Next
    intClientID = objShell.RegRead(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;HKLM\PYGZbs{}\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;amp;strKeyPath\PYGZam{}amp;amp;\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZbs{}\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;amp;strValueName)
    If Err.Number \PYGZam{}amp;lt;\PYGZam{}amp;gt; 0 Then
            SensorRandomizeGetTaniumComputerID = 0
    Else
            SensorRandomizeGetTaniumComputerID = SensorRandomizeReinterpretSignedAsUnsigned(intClientID)
    End If
    On Error Goto 0
End Function \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;SensorRandomizeGetTaniumComputerID

Function SensorRandomizeReinterpretSignedAsUnsigned(ByVal x)
      If x \PYGZam{}amp;lt; 0 Then x = x + 2\PYGZca{}32
      SensorRandomizeReinterpretSignedAsUnsigned = x
End Function \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;SensorRandomizeReinterpretSignedAsUnsigned

Takes regular expression to match.
Example: C:\PYGZbs{}WINDOWS\PYGZbs{}System32\PYGZlt{}/description\PYGZgt{}\PYGZlt{}string\PYGZus{}hints /\PYGZgt{}\PYGZlt{}subcolumns /\PYGZgt{}\PYGZlt{}metadata\PYGZgt{}\PYGZlt{}item\PYGZgt{}\PYGZlt{}admin\PYGZus{}flag\PYGZgt{}0\PYGZlt{}/admin\PYGZus{}flag\PYGZgt{}\PYGZlt{}name\PYGZgt{}defined\PYGZlt{}/name\PYGZgt{}\PYGZlt{}value\PYGZgt{}McAfee\PYGZlt{}/value\PYGZgt{}\PYGZlt{}/item\PYGZgt{}\PYGZlt{}/metadata\PYGZgt{}\PYGZlt{}parameters /\PYGZgt{}\PYGZlt{}queries\PYGZgt{}\PYGZlt{}query\PYGZgt{}\PYGZlt{}platform\PYGZgt{}Windows\PYGZlt{}/platform\PYGZgt{}\PYGZlt{}script\PYGZus{}type\PYGZgt{}VBScript\PYGZlt{}/script\PYGZus{}type\PYGZgt{}\PYGZlt{}signature /\PYGZgt{}\PYGZlt{}script\PYGZgt{}\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;========================================
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; Folder Name Search with RegEx Match
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;========================================
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;@INCLUDE=utils/SensorRandomization/SensorRandomizationFunctions.vbs
Option Explicit

SensorRandomize()

Dim Pattern,strRegExp,strGlobalArg,strCaseSensitiveArg
Dim bGlobal,bCaseSensitive

Pattern = unescape(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\textbar{}\textbar{}dirname\textbar{}\textbar{}\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)
strRegExp = Trim(Unescape(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\textbar{}\textbar{}regexp\textbar{}\textbar{}\PYGZam{}amp;quot;))
strGlobalArg = Trim(Unescape(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\textbar{}\textbar{}global\textbar{}\textbar{}\PYGZam{}amp;quot;))
strCaseSensitiveArg = Trim(Unescape(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\textbar{}\textbar{}casesensitive\textbar{}\textbar{}\PYGZam{}amp;quot;))

bGlobal = GetTrueFalseArg(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;global\PYGZam{}amp;quot;,strGlobalArg)
bCaseSensitive = GetTrueFalseArg(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;casesensitive\PYGZam{}amp;quot;,strCaseSensitiveArg)

Const SYSTEM\PYGZus{}FOLDER = 1, TEMP\PYGZus{}FOLDER = 2, FOR\PYGZus{}READING = 1

Dim FSO, WshShell, Drives, Drive, TextStream, OutputFilename, strLine

Set FSO = CreateObject(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;Scripting.FileSystemObject\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)
Set WshShell = CreateObject(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;WScript.Shell\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)

OutputFilename = TempName() \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; a temporary file in system\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;s temp dir

\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; Go through file system, refresh output file for filename
If Not FSO.FileExists(OutputFilename) Then

    If FSO.FileExists(OutputFilename) Then FSO.DeleteFile OutputFilename

    \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; Get the collection of local drives.
    Set Drives = FSO.Drives
    For Each Drive in Drives
            If Drive.DriveType = 2 Then \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; 2 = Fixed drive
                    \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; Run the Dir command that looks for the filename pattern.
                    RunCommand \PYGZam{}amp;quot;dir \PYGZam{}amp;quot; \PYGZam{}amp;amp;Chr(34)\PYGZam{}amp;amp; Drive.DriveLetter \PYGZam{}amp;amp; \PYGZam{}amp;quot;:\PYGZbs{}\PYGZam{}amp;quot; \PYGZam{}amp;amp; Pattern \PYGZam{}amp;amp; Chr(34)\PYGZam{}amp;amp;\PYGZam{}amp;quot; /a:D /B /S\PYGZam{}amp;quot;, OutputFilename, true
            End If
    Next
End If

\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; Open the output file, echo each line, and then close and delete it.
Set TextStream = FSO.OpenTextFile(OutputFileName, FOR\PYGZus{}READING)
Do While Not TextStream.AtEndOfStream
    strLine = TextStream.ReadLine()
    If RegExpMatch(strRegExp,strLine,bGlobal,bCaseSensitive) Then
            WScript.Echo strLine
    End If
Loop


TextStream.Close()

If FSO.FileExists(OutputFileName) Then
    On Error Resume Next
    FSO.DeleteFile OutputFileName, True
    On Error Goto 0
End If

Function RegExpMatch(strPattern,strToMatch,bGlobal,bIsCaseSensitive)

    Dim re
    Set re = New RegExp
    With re
      .Pattern = strPattern
      .Global = bGlobal
      .IgnoreCase = Not bIsCaseSensitive
    End With

    RegExpMatch = re.Test(strToMatch)

End Function \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;RegExpMatch


Function GetTrueFalseArg(strArgName,strArgValue)
    \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; Checks for valid values, will fail with error message

    Dim bArgVal
    bArgVal = False
    Select Case LCase(strArgValue)
            Case \PYGZam{}amp;quot;true\PYGZam{}amp;quot;
                    bArgVal = True
            Case \PYGZam{}amp;quot;yes\PYGZam{}amp;quot;
                    bArgVal = True
            Case \PYGZam{}amp;quot;false\PYGZam{}amp;quot;
                    bArgVal = False
            Case \PYGZam{}amp;quot;no\PYGZam{}amp;quot;
                    bArgVal = False
            Case Else
                    WScript.Echo \PYGZam{}amp;quot;Error: Argument \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;amp;strArgName\PYGZam{}amp;amp;\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; must be True or False, quitting\PYGZam{}amp;quot;
                    PrintUsage
    End Select
    GetTrueFalseArg = bArgVal

End Function \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;GetTrueFalseArg


\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; Returns the name of a temporary file in the Temp directory.
Function TempName()
    Dim Result
    Do
            Result = FSO.BuildPath(FSO.GetSpecialFolder(TEMP\PYGZus{}FOLDER), FSO.GetTempName())
            WScript.Sleep 200 \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;avoid potential busy loop
    Loop While FSO.FileExists(Result)

    TempName = Result
End Function \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;TempName

\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; Runs a command with Cmd.exe and redirects its output to a temporary
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; file. The function returns the name of the temporary file that holds
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; the command\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;s output.
Function RunCommand(Command, OutputFilename, b64BitNecessary)
    \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; 64BitNecessary true when you need to examine the 64\PYGZhy{}bit areas like system32
    Dim CommandLine,WshShell,strPRogramFilesx86,strDOSCall,objFSO
    Set objFSO = CreateObject(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;Scripting.FileSystemObject\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)
    Set WshShell = CreateObject(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;WScript.Shell\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)

    strDOSCall = \PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZpc{}ComSpec\PYGZpc{} /C \PYGZam{}amp;quot;

    \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; if 64\PYGZhy{}bit OS *and* we must examine in 64\PYGZhy{}bit mode to avoid FS Redirection
    strProgramFilesx86=WshShell.ExpandEnvironmentStrings(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZpc{}ProgramFiles\PYGZpc{}\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)
    If objFSO.FolderExists(strProgramFilesx86) And b64BitNecessary Then \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; quick check for x64
            strDOSCall = FixFileSystemRedirectionForPath(WshShell.ExpandEnvironmentStrings(strDOSCall))
    End If

    CommandLine = WshShell.ExpandEnvironmentStrings(strDOSCall \PYGZam{}amp;amp; Command \PYGZam{}amp;amp; \PYGZam{}amp;quot; \PYGZam{}amp;gt;\PYGZam{}amp;gt; \PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;quot; \PYGZam{}amp;amp; OutputFileName \PYGZam{}amp;amp; \PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)
    WshShell.Run CommandLine, 0, True
End Function \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;RunCommand

Function FixFileSystemRedirectionForPath(strFilePath)
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; This function will fix a folder location so that
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; a 32\PYGZhy{}bit program can be passed the windows\PYGZbs{}system32 directory
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; as a parameter.
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; Even if the sensor or action runs in 64\PYGZhy{}bit mode, a 32\PYGZhy{}bit
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; program called in a 64\PYGZhy{}bit environment cannot access
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; the system32 directory \PYGZhy{} it would be redirected to syswow64.
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; you would not want to do this for 64\PYGZhy{}bit programs.

    Dim objFSO, strSystem32Location,objShell
    Dim strProgramFilesx86,strNewSystem32Location,strRestOfPath
    Set objFSO = CreateObject(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;Scripting.FileSystemObject\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)
    Set objShell = CreateObject(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;Wscript.Shell\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)

    strProgramFilesx86=objShell.ExpandEnvironmentStrings(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZpc{}ProgramFiles\PYGZpc{}\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)

    strFilePath = LCase(strFilePath)
    strSystem32Location = LCase(objFSO.GetSpecialFolder(1))
    strProgramFilesx86=objShell.ExpandEnvironmentStrings(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZpc{}ProgramFiles(x86)\PYGZpc{}\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)

Function SensorRandomizeRandomSleep(intSleepTime)
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; sleeps for a random period of time, intSleepTime is in seconds
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; if the sensor randomize flag is on
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; RandomizeScalingFactor is a multiplier on the values hardcoded in the sensor
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; not typically set but can adjust timings per endpoint, optionally
    Dim intSensorRandomizeWaitTime
    Dim objShell,intRandomizeFlag,strRandomizeRegPath,intRandomizeScalingPercentage
    strRandomizeRegPath = SensorRandomizeGetTaniumRegistryPath\PYGZam{}amp;amp;\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZbs{}Sensor Data\PYGZbs{}Random Sleep\PYGZam{}amp;quot;

    Set objShell = CreateObject(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;WScript.Shell\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)
    On Error Resume Next
    intRandomizeFlag = objShell.RegRead(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;HKLM\PYGZbs{}\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;amp;strRandomizeRegPath\PYGZam{}amp;amp;\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZbs{}SensorRandomizeFlag\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)
    intRandomizeScalingPercentage = objShell.RegRead(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;HKLM\PYGZbs{}\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;amp;strRandomizeRegPath\PYGZam{}amp;amp;\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZbs{}SensorRandomizeScalingPercentage\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)
    On Error Goto 0
    If intRandomizeFlag \PYGZam{}amp;gt; 0 Then
            If intRandomizeScalingPercentage \PYGZam{}amp;gt; 0 Then
                    intSleepTime = intRandomizeScalingPercentage * .01 * intSleepTime
                    SensorRandomizeEcho \PYGZam{}amp;quot;Randomize scaling percentage of \PYGZam{}amp;quot; \PYGZus{}
                            \PYGZam{}amp;amp; intRandomizeScalingPercentage \PYGZam{}amp;amp; \PYGZam{}amp;quot; applied, new sleep time is \PYGZam{}amp;quot; \PYGZam{}amp;amp; intSleepTime
            End If
            intSensorRandomizeWaitTime = CLng(intSleepTime) * 1000 \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; convert to milliseconds
            \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; wait random interval between 0 and the max
            Randomize(SensorRandomizeTaniumRandomSeed)
            \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; assign random value to wait time max value
            intSensorRandomizeWaitTime = Int( ( intSensorRandomizeWaitTime + 1 ) * Rnd )
            SensorRandomizeEcho \PYGZam{}amp;quot;Sleeping for \PYGZam{}amp;quot; \PYGZam{}amp;amp; intSensorRandomizeWaitTime \PYGZam{}amp;amp; \PYGZam{}amp;quot; milliseconds\PYGZam{}amp;quot;
            WScript.Sleep(intSensorRandomizeWaitTime)
            SensorRandomizeEcho \PYGZam{}amp;quot;Done sleeping, continuing ...\PYGZam{}amp;quot;
    Else
            SensorRandomizeEcho \PYGZam{}amp;quot;SensorRandomize Not Enabled \PYGZhy{} No Op\PYGZam{}amp;quot;
    End If
End Function \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;SensorRandomizeRandomSleep

    Dim timerNum

Function SensorRandomizeGetTaniumRegistryPath
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;SensorRandomizeGetTaniumRegistryPath works in x64 or x32

    Dim objShell

    On Error Resume Next

Pattern = unescape(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\textbar{}\textbar{}dirname\textbar{}\textbar{}\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)
strRegExp = Trim(Unescape(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\textbar{}\textbar{}regexp\textbar{}\textbar{}\PYGZam{}amp;quot;))
strGlobalArg = Trim(Unescape(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\textbar{}\textbar{}global\textbar{}\textbar{}\PYGZam{}amp;quot;))
strCaseSensitiveArg = Trim(Unescape(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\textbar{}\textbar{}casesensitive\textbar{}\textbar{}\PYGZam{}amp;quot;))

bGlobal = GetTrueFalseArg(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;global\PYGZam{}amp;quot;,strGlobalArg)
bCaseSensitive = GetTrueFalseArg(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;casesensitive\PYGZam{}amp;quot;,strCaseSensitiveArg)

Const SYSTEM\PYGZus{}FOLDER = 1, TEMP\PYGZus{}FOLDER = 2, FOR\PYGZus{}READING = 1

Dim FSO, WshShell, Drives, Drive, TextStream, OutputFilename, strLine

Set FSO = CreateObject(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;Scripting.FileSystemObject\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)
Set WshShell = CreateObject(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;WScript.Shell\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)

OutputFilename = TempName() \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; a temporary file in system\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;s temp dir

\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; Go through file system, refresh output file for filename
If Not FSO.FileExists(OutputFilename) Then

    If FSO.FileExists(OutputFilename) Then FSO.DeleteFile OutputFilename

    \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; Get the collection of local drives.
    Set Drives = FSO.Drives
    For Each Drive in Drives
            If Drive.DriveType = 2 Then \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; 2 = Fixed drive
                    \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; Run the Dir command that looks for the filename pattern.
                    RunCommand \PYGZam{}amp;quot;dir \PYGZam{}amp;quot; \PYGZam{}amp;amp;Chr(34)\PYGZam{}amp;amp; Drive.DriveLetter \PYGZam{}amp;amp; \PYGZam{}amp;quot;:\PYGZbs{}\PYGZam{}amp;quot; \PYGZam{}amp;amp; Pattern \PYGZam{}amp;amp; Chr(34)\PYGZam{}amp;amp;\PYGZam{}amp;quot; /a:D /B /S\PYGZam{}amp;quot;, OutputFilename, true
            End If
    Next
End If

\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; Open the output file, echo each line, and then close and delete it.
Set TextStream = FSO.OpenTextFile(OutputFileName, FOR\PYGZus{}READING)
Do While Not TextStream.AtEndOfStream
    strLine = TextStream.ReadLine()
    If RegExpMatch(strRegExp,strLine,bGlobal,bCaseSensitive) Then
            WScript.Echo strLine
    End If
Loop


TextStream.Close()

If FSO.FileExists(OutputFileName) Then
    On Error Resume Next
    FSO.DeleteFile OutputFileName, True
    On Error Goto 0
End If

Function RegExpMatch(strPattern,strToMatch,bGlobal,bIsCaseSensitive)

    Dim re
    Set re = New RegExp
    With re
      .Pattern = strPattern
      .Global = bGlobal
      .IgnoreCase = Not bIsCaseSensitive
    End With

    RegExpMatch = re.Test(strToMatch)

End Function \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;RegExpMatch


Function GetTrueFalseArg(strArgName,strArgValue)
    \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; Checks for valid values, will fail with error message

    Dim bArgVal
    bArgVal = False
    Select Case LCase(strArgValue)
            Case \PYGZam{}amp;quot;true\PYGZam{}amp;quot;
                    bArgVal = True
            Case \PYGZam{}amp;quot;yes\PYGZam{}amp;quot;
                    bArgVal = True
            Case \PYGZam{}amp;quot;false\PYGZam{}amp;quot;
                    bArgVal = False
            Case \PYGZam{}amp;quot;no\PYGZam{}amp;quot;
                    bArgVal = False
            Case Else
                    WScript.Echo \PYGZam{}amp;quot;Error: Argument \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;amp;strArgName\PYGZam{}amp;amp;\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; must be True or False, quitting\PYGZam{}amp;quot;
                    PrintUsage
    End Select
    GetTrueFalseArg = bArgVal

End Function \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;GetTrueFalseArg


\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; Returns the name of a temporary file in the Temp directory.
Function TempName()
    Dim Result
    Do
            Result = FSO.BuildPath(FSO.GetSpecialFolder(TEMP\PYGZus{}FOLDER), FSO.GetTempName())
            WScript.Sleep 200 \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;avoid potential busy loop
    Loop While FSO.FileExists(Result)

    TempName = Result
End Function \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;TempName

\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; Runs a command with Cmd.exe and redirects its output to a temporary
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; file. The function returns the name of the temporary file that holds
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; the command\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;s output.
Function RunCommand(Command, OutputFilename, b64BitNecessary)
    \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; 64BitNecessary true when you need to examine the 64\PYGZhy{}bit areas like system32
    Dim CommandLine,WshShell,strPRogramFilesx86,strDOSCall,objFSO
    Set objFSO = CreateObject(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;Scripting.FileSystemObject\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)
    Set WshShell = CreateObject(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;WScript.Shell\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)

    strDOSCall = \PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZpc{}ComSpec\PYGZpc{} /C \PYGZam{}amp;quot;

    \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; if 64\PYGZhy{}bit OS *and* we must examine in 64\PYGZhy{}bit mode to avoid FS Redirection
    strProgramFilesx86=WshShell.ExpandEnvironmentStrings(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZpc{}ProgramFiles\PYGZpc{}\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)
    If objFSO.FolderExists(strProgramFilesx86) And b64BitNecessary Then \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; quick check for x64
            strDOSCall = FixFileSystemRedirectionForPath(WshShell.ExpandEnvironmentStrings(strDOSCall))
    End If

    CommandLine = WshShell.ExpandEnvironmentStrings(strDOSCall \PYGZam{}amp;amp; Command \PYGZam{}amp;amp; \PYGZam{}amp;quot; \PYGZam{}amp;gt;\PYGZam{}amp;gt; \PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;quot; \PYGZam{}amp;amp; OutputFileName \PYGZam{}amp;amp; \PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)
    WshShell.Run CommandLine, 0, True
End Function \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;RunCommand

Function FixFileSystemRedirectionForPath(strFilePath)
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; This function will fix a folder location so that
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; a 32\PYGZhy{}bit program can be passed the windows\PYGZbs{}system32 directory
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; as a parameter.
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; Even if the sensor or action runs in 64\PYGZhy{}bit mode, a 32\PYGZhy{}bit
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; program called in a 64\PYGZhy{}bit environment cannot access
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; the system32 directory \PYGZhy{} it would be redirected to syswow64.
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; you would not want to do this for 64\PYGZhy{}bit programs.

    Dim objFSO, strSystem32Location,objShell
    Dim strProgramFilesx86,strNewSystem32Location,strRestOfPath
    Set objFSO = CreateObject(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;Scripting.FileSystemObject\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)
    Set objShell = CreateObject(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;Wscript.Shell\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)

    strProgramFilesx86=objShell.ExpandEnvironmentStrings(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZpc{}ProgramFiles\PYGZpc{}\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)

    strFilePath = LCase(strFilePath)
    strSystem32Location = LCase(objFSO.GetSpecialFolder(1))
    strProgramFilesx86=objShell.ExpandEnvironmentStrings(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZpc{}ProgramFiles(x86)\PYGZpc{}\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)

    If objFSO.FolderExists(strProgramFilesx86) Then \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; quick check for x64
            If InStr(strFilePath,strSystem32Location) = 1 Then
                    strRestOfPath = Replace(strFilePath,strSystem32Location,\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)
                    strNewSystem32Location = Replace(strSystem32Location,\PYGZam{}amp;quot;system32\PYGZam{}amp;quot;,\PYGZam{}amp;quot;sysnative\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)
                    strFilePath = strNewSystem32Location\PYGZam{}amp;amp;strRestOfPath
            End If
    End If
    FixFileSystemRedirectionForPath = strFilePath

    \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;Cleanup
    Set objFSO = Nothing
End Function \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;FixFileSystemRedirectionForPath

Function SensorRandomizeRandomSleep(intSleepTime)
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; sleeps for a random period of time, intSleepTime is in seconds
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; if the sensor randomize flag is on
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; RandomizeScalingFactor is a multiplier on the values hardcoded in the sensor
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; not typically set but can adjust timings per endpoint, optionally
    Dim intSensorRandomizeWaitTime
    Dim objShell,intRandomizeFlag,strRandomizeRegPath,intRandomizeScalingPercentage
    strRandomizeRegPath = SensorRandomizeGetTaniumRegistryPath\PYGZam{}amp;amp;\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZbs{}Sensor Data\PYGZbs{}Random Sleep\PYGZam{}amp;quot;

    Set objShell = CreateObject(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;WScript.Shell\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)
    On Error Resume Next
    intRandomizeFlag = objShell.RegRead(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;HKLM\PYGZbs{}\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;amp;strRandomizeRegPath\PYGZam{}amp;amp;\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZbs{}SensorRandomizeFlag\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)
    intRandomizeScalingPercentage = objShell.RegRead(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;HKLM\PYGZbs{}\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;amp;strRandomizeRegPath\PYGZam{}amp;amp;\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZbs{}SensorRandomizeScalingPercentage\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)
    On Error Goto 0
    If intRandomizeFlag \PYGZam{}amp;gt; 0 Then
            If intRandomizeScalingPercentage \PYGZam{}amp;gt; 0 Then
                    intSleepTime = intRandomizeScalingPercentage * .01 * intSleepTime
                    SensorRandomizeEcho \PYGZam{}amp;quot;Randomize scaling percentage of \PYGZam{}amp;quot; \PYGZus{}
                            \PYGZam{}amp;amp; intRandomizeScalingPercentage \PYGZam{}amp;amp; \PYGZam{}amp;quot; applied, new sleep time is \PYGZam{}amp;quot; \PYGZam{}amp;amp; intSleepTime
            End If
            intSensorRandomizeWaitTime = CLng(intSleepTime) * 1000 \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; convert to milliseconds
            \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; wait random interval between 0 and the max
            Randomize(SensorRandomizeTaniumRandomSeed)
            \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; assign random value to wait time max value
            intSensorRandomizeWaitTime = Int( ( intSensorRandomizeWaitTime + 1 ) * Rnd )
            SensorRandomizeEcho \PYGZam{}amp;quot;Sleeping for \PYGZam{}amp;quot; \PYGZam{}amp;amp; intSensorRandomizeWaitTime \PYGZam{}amp;amp; \PYGZam{}amp;quot; milliseconds\PYGZam{}amp;quot;
            WScript.Sleep(intSensorRandomizeWaitTime)
            SensorRandomizeEcho \PYGZam{}amp;quot;Done sleeping, continuing ...\PYGZam{}amp;quot;
    Else
            SensorRandomizeEcho \PYGZam{}amp;quot;SensorRandomize Not Enabled \PYGZhy{} No Op\PYGZam{}amp;quot;
    End If
End Function \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;SensorRandomizeRandomSleep

Function SensorRandomizeTaniumRandomSeed
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; for randomizing sensor code, the default seed is not random enough
    Dim timerNum
    timerNum = Timer()
    If timerNum \PYGZam{}amp;lt; 1 Then
            SensorRandomizeTaniumRandomSeed = (SensorRandomizeGetTaniumComputerID / Timer() * 10 )
    Else
            SensorRandomizeTaniumRandomSeed = SensorRandomizeGetTaniumComputerID / Timer
    End If
End Function \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;SensorRandomizeTaniumRandomSeed

Function SensorRandomizeGetTaniumRegistryPath
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;SensorRandomizeGetTaniumRegistryPath works in x64 or x32
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;looks for a valid Path value

    Dim objShell
    Dim keyNativePath, keyWoWPath, strPath, strFoundTaniumRegistryPath

    Set objShell = CreateObject(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;WScript.Shell\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)

    keyNativePath = \PYGZam{}amp;quot;Software\PYGZbs{}Tanium\PYGZbs{}Tanium Client\PYGZam{}amp;quot;
    keyWoWPath = \PYGZam{}amp;quot;Software\PYGZbs{}Wow6432Node\PYGZbs{}Tanium\PYGZbs{}Tanium Client\PYGZam{}amp;quot;

    \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; first check the Software key (valid for 32\PYGZhy{}bit machines, or 64\PYGZhy{}bit machines in 32\PYGZhy{}bit mode)
    On Error Resume Next
    strPath = objShell.RegRead(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;HKLM\PYGZbs{}\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;amp;keyNativePath\PYGZam{}amp;amp;\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZbs{}Path\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)
    On Error Goto 0
    strFoundTaniumRegistryPath = keyNativePath

    If strPath = \PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;quot; Then
            \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; Could not find 32\PYGZhy{}bit mode path, checking Wow6432Node
            On Error Resume Next
            strPath = objShell.RegRead(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;HKLM\PYGZbs{}\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;amp;keyWoWPath\PYGZam{}amp;amp;\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZbs{}Path\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)
            On Error Goto 0
            strFoundTaniumRegistryPath = keyWoWPath
    End If

    If Not strPath = \PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;quot; Then
            SensorRandomizeGetTaniumRegistryPath = strFoundTaniumRegistryPath
    Else
            SensorRandomizeGetTaniumRegistryPath = False
            WScript.Echo \PYGZam{}amp;quot;Error: Cannot locate Tanium Registry Path\PYGZam{}amp;quot;
    End If
End Function \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;SensorRandomizeGetTaniumRegistryPath

Function SensorRandomizeGetTaniumComputerID
\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039; This function gets the Tanium Computer ID
    Dim objShell
    Dim intClientID,strID,strKeyPath,strValueName

    strKeyPath = SensorRandomizeGetTaniumRegistryPath
    strValueName = \PYGZam{}amp;quot;ComputerID\PYGZam{}amp;quot;
    Set objShell = CreateObject(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;WScript.Shell\PYGZam{}amp;quot;)
    On Error Resume Next
    intClientID = objShell.RegRead(\PYGZam{}amp;quot;HKLM\PYGZbs{}\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;amp;strKeyPath\PYGZam{}amp;amp;\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZbs{}\PYGZam{}amp;quot;\PYGZam{}amp;amp;strValueName)
    If Err.Number \PYGZam{}amp;lt;\PYGZam{}amp;gt; 0 Then
            SensorRandomizeGetTaniumComputerID = 0
    Else
            SensorRandomizeGetTaniumComputerID = SensorRandomizeReinterpretSignedAsUnsigned(intClientID)
    End If
    On Error Goto 0
End Function \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;SensorRandomizeGetTaniumComputerID

Function SensorRandomizeReinterpretSignedAsUnsigned(ByVal x)
      If x \PYGZam{}amp;lt; 0 Then x = x + 2\PYGZca{}32
      SensorRandomizeReinterpretSignedAsUnsigned = x
End Function \PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZsh{}039;SensorRandomizeReinterpretSignedAsUnsigned

            If Drive.DriveType = 2 Then \PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; 2 = Fixed drive
                    \PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; Run the Dir command that looks for the filename pattern.
                    RunCommand \PYGZam{}quot;dir \PYGZam{}quot; \PYGZam{}amp;Chr(34)\PYGZam{}amp; Drive.DriveLetter \PYGZam{}amp; \PYGZam{}quot;:\PYGZbs{}\PYGZam{}quot; \PYGZam{}amp; Pattern \PYGZam{}amp; Chr(34)\PYGZam{}amp;\PYGZam{}quot; /a:D /B /S\PYGZam{}quot;, OutputFilename, true
            End If
    Next
End If

\PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; Open the output file, echo each line, and then close and delete it.
Set TextStream = FSO.OpenTextFile(OutputFileName, FOR\PYGZus{}READING)
Do While Not TextStream.AtEndOfStream
    strLine = TextStream.ReadLine()
    If RegExpMatch(strRegExp,strLine,bGlobal,bCaseSensitive) Then
            WScript.Echo strLine
    End If
Loop


TextStream.Close()

If FSO.FileExists(OutputFileName) Then
    On Error Resume Next
    FSO.DeleteFile OutputFileName, True
    On Error Goto 0
End If

Function RegExpMatch(strPattern,strToMatch,bGlobal,bIsCaseSensitive)

    Dim re
    Set re = New RegExp
    With re
      .Pattern = strPattern
      .Global = bGlobal
      .IgnoreCase = Not bIsCaseSensitive
    End With

    RegExpMatch = re.Test(strToMatch)

End Function \PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039;RegExpMatch

\PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; Runs a command with Cmd.exe and redirects its output to a temporary
\PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; file. The function returns the name of the temporary file that holds
\PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; the command\PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039;s output.
Function RunCommand(Command, OutputFilename, b64BitNecessary)
    \PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; 64BitNecessary true when you need to examine the 64\PYGZhy{}bit areas like system32
    Dim CommandLine,WshShell,strPRogramFilesx86,strDOSCall,objFSO
    Set objFSO = CreateObject(\PYGZam{}quot;Scripting.FileSystemObject\PYGZam{}quot;)
    Set WshShell = CreateObject(\PYGZam{}quot;WScript.Shell\PYGZam{}quot;)

    strDOSCall = \PYGZam{}quot;\PYGZpc{}ComSpec\PYGZpc{} /C \PYGZam{}quot;

    \PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; if 64\PYGZhy{}bit OS *and* we must examine in 64\PYGZhy{}bit mode to avoid FS Redirection
    strProgramFilesx86=WshShell.ExpandEnvironmentStrings(\PYGZam{}quot;\PYGZpc{}ProgramFiles\PYGZpc{}\PYGZam{}quot;)
    If objFSO.FolderExists(strProgramFilesx86) And b64BitNecessary Then \PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; quick check for x64
            strDOSCall = FixFileSystemRedirectionForPath(WshShell.ExpandEnvironmentStrings(strDOSCall))
    End If

    CommandLine = WshShell.ExpandEnvironmentStrings(strDOSCall \PYGZam{}amp; Command \PYGZam{}amp; \PYGZam{}quot; \PYGZam{}gt;\PYGZam{}gt; \PYGZam{}quot;\PYGZam{}quot;\PYGZam{}quot; \PYGZam{}amp; OutputFileName \PYGZam{}amp; \PYGZam{}quot;\PYGZam{}quot;\PYGZam{}quot;\PYGZam{}quot;)
    WshShell.Run CommandLine, 0, True
End Function \PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039;RunCommand

Function FixFileSystemRedirectionForPath(strFilePath)
\PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; This function will fix a folder location so that
\PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; a 32\PYGZhy{}bit program can be passed the windows\PYGZbs{}system32 directory
\PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; as a parameter.
\PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; Even if the sensor or action runs in 64\PYGZhy{}bit mode, a 32\PYGZhy{}bit
\PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; program called in a 64\PYGZhy{}bit environment cannot access
\PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; the system32 directory \PYGZhy{} it would be redirected to syswow64.
\PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; you would not want to do this for 64\PYGZhy{}bit programs.

    Dim objFSO, strSystem32Location,objShell
    Dim strProgramFilesx86,strNewSystem32Location,strRestOfPath
    Set objFSO = CreateObject(\PYGZam{}quot;Scripting.FileSystemObject\PYGZam{}quot;)
    Set objShell = CreateObject(\PYGZam{}quot;Wscript.Shell\PYGZam{}quot;)

    strProgramFilesx86=objShell.ExpandEnvironmentStrings(\PYGZam{}quot;\PYGZpc{}ProgramFiles\PYGZpc{}\PYGZam{}quot;)

    strFilePath = LCase(strFilePath)
    strSystem32Location = LCase(objFSO.GetSpecialFolder(1))
    strProgramFilesx86=objShell.ExpandEnvironmentStrings(\PYGZam{}quot;\PYGZpc{}ProgramFiles(x86)\PYGZpc{}\PYGZam{}quot;)

    If objFSO.FolderExists(strProgramFilesx86) Then \PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039; quick check for x64
            If InStr(strFilePath,strSystem32Location) = 1 Then
                    strRestOfPath = Replace(strFilePath,strSystem32Location,\PYGZam{}quot;\PYGZam{}quot;)
                    strNewSystem32Location = Replace(strSystem32Location,\PYGZam{}quot;system32\PYGZam{}quot;,\PYGZam{}quot;sysnative\PYGZam{}quot;)
                    strFilePath = strNewSystem32Location\PYGZam{}amp;strRestOfPath
            End If
    End If
    FixFileSystemRedirectionForPath = strFilePath

    \PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039;Cleanup
    Set objFSO = Nothing
End Function \PYGZam{}\PYGZsh{}039;FixFileSystemRedirectionForPath
